Gulp:
    - Gulp is the Automation tool used to prepare the Production Builds.

    - Gulp based on NodeJS

Installation Of Gulp:
---------------------

>npm install -g gulp


Modules in Gulp:
----------------

1. gulp-concat

    - this module used to concat the files.

2. gulp-uglify

    - this module used to compress the javascript files

3.gulp-minify-html

    - this module used to compress the html files.


4. gulp-minify-css

    - this module used to compress the css files.

5. gulp-bower

    - used to execute the bower.

6. gulp-open

    - used to launch the browsers.


- we can download the above modules by using "package.json" file.

- we can execute the "package.json" file by using "npm install" command

------------
GulpDemo
    devEnv
        html
            index_one.html
            index_two.html
        css
            style_one.css
            style_two.css

        js
            sample_one.js
            sample_two.js

        index.html

        bower.json
------------------------------

Gulpfile.js
-----------

//import the modules
var concat = require("gulp-concat");
var uglify = require("gulp-uglify");
var minifyHTML = require("gulp-minify-html");
var minifyCSS = require("gulp-minify-css");
var bower = require("gulp-bower");
var open = require("gulp-open");
var gulp = require("gulp");


gulp.task("task_one" , function(){
    gulp.src("./devEnv/html/*.html")
        .pipe(concat("final.min.html"))
        .pipe(minifyHTML())
        .pipe(gulp.dest("./prodEnv/html"));
});

>gulp task_one

























